  "prompt": "The current year is 2014. Why is this the 21st century and not the 20th century?",
  "response": "The numbering of centuries can be a bit confusing. The 21st century includes the years from 2001 to 2100, while the 20th century includes the years from 1901 to 2000. \n\nThe reason for this is that centuries are defined based on the year numbers, which start from year 1. There is no year 0 in the Gregorian calendar system, which means that the first century was from the year 1 to 100, the second century from 101 to 200, and so on. Consequently, the 21st century began in the year 2001 and will end in the year 2100. Thus, even though we are in the year 2014, we are actually in the 21st century.",
